ano)|Mount Wenchi]]\n\n== Y ==\n[[Mount Yerer]]\n\n== Z ==\n[[Mount Zuqualla]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Amba (geology)]]\n* [[List of volcanoes in Ethiopia]]\n* [[List of highest mountain peaks of Africa]], with data on the 47 highest mountains of Ethiopia\n\n{{Africa topic|List of mountains in}}\n[[Category:Lists of landforms of Ethiopia|Mountains]]\n[[Category:Lists of mountains by country|Ethiopia]]\n[[Category:Mountains of Ethiopia| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe following notable mountains and mountain ranges are completely or partially within the borders of [[Ethiopia]]:\n__NOTOC__\n== A ==\n[[Mount Abba Yared]] \u2022 [[Abul Kasim (mountain)]] \u2022 [[Mount Abuna Yosef]] \u2022 [[Mount Abuye Meda]] \u2022 [[Amba Alagi]] \u2022 [[Ale Bagu]] \u2022 [[Mount Amara]] \u2022 [[Amaro Mountains]] \u2022 [[Mount Ambaricho]] \u2022 [[Mount Amedamit]] \u2022 [[Amba Aradam]] \u2022 [[Mount Asimba]] \u2022 [[Mount Ayalu]]\n\n== B ==\n[[Bale Mountains]] \u2022 [[Mount Bambasi]] \u2022 [[Mount Batu]] \u2022 [[Mount Belaya]] \u2022 [[Mount Biuat]] \u2022 [[Borale Ale]] \u2022 [[Borawli]]\n\n== C ==\n[[Mount Chilalo]] \u2022 [[Mount Choqa]] \u2022 [[Choqa Mountains]]\n\n== D ==\n[[Dangur range]] \u2022 [[Mount Dara Tiniro]] \u2022 [[Mount Darkeena]] \u2022 [[Debre Damo]] \u2022 [[Mount Delo]] \u2022 [[Mount Dendi]]\n\n== E ==\n[[Entoto Mountains]] \u2022 [[Mount Entoto]] \u2022 [[Erta Ale Range]] \u2022 [[Ethiopian Highlands]] \n\n== F ==\n[[Mount Fentale]] \u2022 [[Mount Amba Ferit]] \u2022 [[Mount Fota]] \u2022 [[Furi]]\n\n== G ==\n[[Gada Ale]] \u2022 [[Mount Gara Muleta]] \u2022 [[Mount Gardolla]] \u2022 [[Mount Garochan]] \u2022 [[Mount Gaysay]] \u2022 [[Amba Geshen]] \u2022 [[Mount Gugu]] \u2022 [[Mount Guna]] \u2022 [[Mount Gurage]]\n\n== H ==\n[[Mount Hai]] \u2022 [[Hayli Gubbi]] \u2022 [[Mount Holla]]\n\n== K ==\n[[Mount Kaka]] \u2022 [[Kulibi]] \u2022 [[Kundudo]]\n\n== M ==\n[[Mount Maigudo]] \u2022 [[Mount Megezez]] \u2022 [[Mou