rs who committed suicide]]\n[[Category:Suicides by hanging in India]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Hyderabad, India]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]9642226257\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian film actor}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| auto               = \n| name               = \n| image              = File:Uday_kiran.jpg\n| caption            = Uday Kiran\n| birth_name         = Vajpeyajula Uday Kiran\n| birth_date         = {{birth date|1980|06|26|df=yes}}<ref name=indtoday/>\n| birth_place        = [[Hyderabad]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]]<br/>(now in [[Telangana]], India)\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|2014|01|05|1980|06|26|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmcircle.com/uday-kiran-dies-orphan/ |title=Hero Uday Kiran Death. |publisher=filmcircle.com |accessdate=6 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107085140/http://filmcircle.com/uday-kiran-dies-orphan/ |archivedate=7 January 2014 }}</ref>\n| death_place        = Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh, India<br/>(now in Telangana, India)\n| death_cause        = Suicide\n| occupation         = Actor\n| credits            = ''[[Nuvvu Nenu]]'' (2001)<br />''[[Chitram]]'' (2000)<br />''[[Manasantha Nuvve]]'' (2001)<br />''[[Nee Sneham]]'' (2002)<br />''[[Kalusukovalani]]'' (2002)<br />''[[Neeku Nenu Naaku Nuvvu]]'' (2003)\n| spouse             = Vishitha (m. 2012\u20142014; his death)\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Uday Kiran''' (born '''Vajpeyajula Uday kiran'''; 26 June 1980 \u2013 5 January 2014) was a [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Award]] winning [[Indian film]] actor, who primarily worked in the [[Telugu cinema]]. His first three films, ''[[Chitram]]'', ''[[Nuvvu Nenu]]'' and ''[[Manasantha Nuvve]]'', were successful hits, earning him the title \"Hat-trick Hero\".<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2003/11/07/stories/2003110701080800.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=I, Me, Myself - Uday Kiran | date=2003-11-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=M. L. Narasimham |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article104963.ece |title=Arts / Cinema : Heart-warming tale |publisher=The Hindu |date=2010-02-12 |accessdate=2012-10-20 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref> ''[[Avunanna Kaadanna]]'' film was the last hit in his career.{{cn|date=July 2019}}\n\nIn 2001, he won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Telugu]]<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2002-04-06/hyderabad/27122602_1_filmfare-film-award-actor-award | work=The Times Of India | title=Nuvvu Nenu wins 4 Filmfare awards | date=6 April 2002}}</ref> for the film ''[[Nuvvu Nenu]]'', and became the youngest winner of the [[Filmfare]] best actor award after Tamil actor [[Kamal Haasan]]. He is the only Telugu actor to have his first four films remade into all regional languages. In 2006, he made his [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] debut with the film ''[[Poi (film)|Poi]]'', directed by veteran [[K. Balachander]].<ref>[http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2006/02/24/stories/2006022401910100.htm The Hindu : Friday Review Hyderabad : A new dawn for Uday<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100809115236/http://hinduonnet.com/thehindu/fr/2006/02/24/stories/2006022401910100.htm |date=9 August 2010 }}</ref> Subsequently, he starred in romantic films including ''[[Nee Sneham]]'' and ''[[Kalusukovalani]]''. His other performances have been in the films ''[[Sreeram]]'', ''[[Avunanna Kaadanna]]'', ''[[Nuvvekaddunte Nenakkadunta]]'' and ''[[Jai Sriram]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/movie-review/19494812.cms |title=Jai Sriram movie review: Wallpaper, Story, Trailer at Times of India |publisher=The Times of India |date=1970-01-01 |accessdate=2013-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2007/09/15/stories/2007091550670100.htm |title=Metro Plus Visakhapatnam / Cinema : Uday Kiran to go by viability |publisher=The India times |date=2007-09-15 |accessdate=2013-04-13 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/92638.html |title=Uday Kiran's 'Jai Sriram' Platinum disc function - Telugu Movie News |publisher=Indiaglitz.com |date= |accessdate=2013-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sakshipost.com/index.php/entertainment/trailers-reviews/16439-jai-sriram-movie-review |title=Jai Sriram - Movie review |publisher=Sakshi Post |date=2012-12-20 |accessdate=2013-04-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130616024425/http://www.sakshipost.com/index.php/entertainment/trailers-reviews/16439-jai-sriram-movie-review |archivedate=16 June 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nUday Kiran was born on 26 June 1980<ref name=indtoday/> to Telugu-speaking Brahmin family of VVK Murthy and  Nirmala. He graduated in commerce from [[Wesley degree college(secunderabad)]]. And he did schooling in K V Picket, near Jubilee Bus Stand.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cinecurry.com/celebzone/telugu/udaykiran |title=Uday Kiran - Videos, Wallpapers, Movies, Photos, Biography |publisher=Cinecurry |date=1980-06-26 |accessdate=2012-10-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308191537/http://www.cinecurry.com/celebzone/telugu/udaykiran |archivedate=8 March 2012 }}</ref>\nKiran was engaged to [[Chiranjeevi]]'s daughter Sushmitha in 2003,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad-times/Uday-Kiran-gets-engaged-to-Chirus-daughter-today/articleshow/43719729.cms |title=Uday Kiran gets engaged to Chiru's daughter today |publisher=timesofindia.com |date=2013-04-18}}</ref> but the engagement was broken.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2003-07-03/hyderabad/27189565_1_chiranjeevi-wedding-allu-aravind |title=Incompatibility hits star wedding |publisher=timesofindia.com |date=2013-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/telugu/interview.php?id=13252967&cid=2410 |title=Marriage is not a priority now: Uday Kiran |publisher=sify.com |date=}}</ref> He married Vishitha on 24 October 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gulte.com/movienews/11366/Uday-Kiran-finds-his-Life-Partner |title=Uday Kiran Marriage on October 24th |publisher=Gulte.com |date=2012-10-11 |accessdate=2012-10-20}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nKiran started modelling while in college. He made his film debut in the [[Hinglish]] film ''[[Mysterious Girl (film)|Mysterious Girl]]'' in 1999.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/hyderabad-times/Ive-to-shed-the-lover-boy-image-Uday/articleshow/16808276.cms|title=I\u2019ve to shed the lover boy image: Uday - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> In 2000, Kiran made his Tollywood debut under his mentor, cinematographer turned film director [[Teja (film director)|Teja]] with the film ''[[Chitram]]'', in which he played the 17-year-old lead character.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telugucinema.com/c/publish/moviereviews/nuvvunenu.php |title=Reviews : Movie Reviews : Nuvvu Nenu |publisher=Telugucinema.com |accessdate=2012-10-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120324235100/http://www.telugucinema.com/c/publish/moviereviews/nuvvunenu.php |archivedate=24 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThis film, followed by two others, ''[[Nuvvu Nenu]]'' and ''[[Manasantha Nuvve]]'', made him among the very few actors in [[Telugu cinema]] to deliver three consecutive successful films. His performance as a hot-blooded youngster in ''Nuvvu Nenu'' won him the [[Filmfare Best Actor Award (Telugu)]] in the year 2001.\n\nIn his fourth film, ''[[Kalusukovalani]]'', he displayed his dancing skills through the songs, \"Udayinchina\" and \"Cheliya Cheliya\". In his fifth film, ''[[Sreeram]]'' he ventured into an action oriented story of a youngster aspiring to become a top cop. 2002 saw him in ''[[Nee Sneham]]'', another blockbuster movie of that year for which he was nominated for [[Filmfare Best Actor Award (Telugu)]] for the second time.\n\nIn 2005, he ventured into Tamil with the film ''[[Poi (film)|Poi]]'' directed by [[K.Balachander]]. He then did two more films, ''[[Vambu Sandai]]'' and ''[[Pen Singam]]'' in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], the latter being the story penned by [[M. Karunanidhi]], which did moderately well at the box office.\n\n==Death==\nUday Kiran died by committing suicide on 5 January 2014.<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news | url=http://filmcircle.com/hero-uday-kiran-died/ | work=Filmcircle.com | title=Hero Uday Kiran no More | date=2014-01-06 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106044016/http://filmcircle.com/hero-uday-kiran-died/ | archivedate=6 January 2014 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> ln the film industry that renowned actor Uday's engagement with Chiranjeevi's daughter had been called off earlier. After breakup,he tried in Tamil with his own production.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chennaivision.com/news/2014/64098.php |title=Telugu actor Uday Kiran commits suicide |date=2014-01-06 |accessdate=2014-01-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109185832/http://www.chennaivision.com/news/2014/64098.php |archivedate=9 January 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Kiran had suffered from depression due to financial crisis for almost a year.<ref>[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140109/news-current-affairs/article/uday-kiran-had-severe-financial-crisis Uday Kiran had severe financial crisis | Deccan Chronicle<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref name=indtoday>[http://www.indtoday.com/tollywood-actor-uday-kiran-commits-suicide/ \"Tollywood actor Uday Kiran commits suicide\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141023065707/http://www.indtoday.com/tollywood-actor-uday-kiran-commits-suicide/ |date=23 October 2014 }}. Intoday. 6 January 2014.</ref> <ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/533244/20140107/uday-kiran-death-blamegame-actor-suicide-ripudaykiran.htm Uday Kiran's Shocking Death: Advocate Blames 'Four' Big Tollywood Camps for Actor's Suicide - International Business Times<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-01-07/news-interviews/45953960_1_uday-kiran-state-human-rights-commission-tollywood The curious case of Uday Kiran & the \u2018Big 4\u2019 - Times Of India<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nOn 6 January 2014, Uday Kiran's body was kept at the ''Andhra Pradesh Film Chamber of Commerce'' and several film personalities including Dasari Narayana Rao, D Rama Naidu Venkatesh, D Suresh Babu, Srikanth, Shivaji, Tanikella Bharani, Chalapathi Rao, Tammareddy Bharadwaja, (Ex) MLA Jaya Sudha, Parachuri Gopalakrishna, Parachuri Venkateshwara Rao, Shivaji Raja, Anup Rubens, Samadra, Kadambari Kiran, Sunil and Anita were among those who paid their last respects to the actor, before being taken to the cremation grounds.<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/tabloid/uday-kiran-s-death-suspicious-case-police/article1-1169813.aspx Uday Kiran's death suspicious case: police - Hindustan Times<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> According to AP police, a young fan of Uday Kiran allegedly committed suicide by hanging himself from a tree at Komatapalli junction in Bobbili sub-division in Vizianagaram.<ref>[http://www.ndtv.com/article/south/upset-over-uday-kiran-s-suicide-fan-ends-life-469429 Upset over Uday Kiran's suicide, fan ends life | NDTV.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Language\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1999 ||''[[Mysterious Girl (film)|Mysterious Girl]]''|| [[Hinglish]] ||  Goutham|| Released in Telugu as  ''Jodi No.1'' (2003)\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Chitram ]]'' || rowspan=\"10\"|Telugu || Ramana ||                  