{"title_page": "Hespererato rehderi", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| taxon =Hespererato rehderi\n| image = \n| image_caption =  \n| authority = (Raines, 2002)\n| synonyms_ref = <ref name=\"WoRMS\" />\n| synonyms =\n* ''Proterato (Sulcerato) rehderi'' <small>Raines, 2002</small>\n* ''Hespererato rehderi'' <small>(Raines, 2002)</small>\n* ''Proterato rehderi'' <small>Raines, 2002</small> (original combination)\n| display_parents = 3\n}}\n\n'''''Hespererato rehderi''''' is a [[species]] of small [[sea snail]], a [[marine (ocean)|marine]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Eratoidae]], the false cowries or trivias.<ref name=\"WoRMS\">MolluscaBase (2018). Hespererato rehderi (Raines, 2002). Accessed through: World Register of Marine Species at: http://marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=567510 on 2018-07-18</ref>\n\n==Description==\n{{Expand section|date=January 2011}}\nThe shell grows to a length of 1.6&nbsp;mm\n\n==Distribution==\nThis species occurs in the Pacific Ocean off [[Easter Island]]\n\n==Notes==\n* Raines. 2002. Contribution to the knowledge of Easter Island Mollusca. Conchiglia 34 (304): 11\u201340\n* Raines, B.K. (2007) New molluscan records from Easter Island, with the description of a new Ethminolia. Visaya, 2(1), 70\u201388. page(s): 81\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q13227902}}\n\n[[Category:Eratoidae]]\n[[Category:Gastropods described in 2002]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of the Pacific Ocean]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| taxon =Hespererato rehderi\n| image = \n| image_caption =  \n| authority = (Raines, 2002)\n| synonyms_ref = <ref name=\"WoRMS\" />\n| synonyms =\n* ''Proterato (Sulcerato) rehderi'' <small>Raines, 2002</small>\n* ''Hespererato rehderi'' <small>(Raines, 2002)</small>\n* ''Proterato rehderi'' <small>Raines, 2002</small> (original combination)\n| display_parents = 3\n}}\n\n'''''Hespererato rehderi''''' is a [[species]] of small [[sea snail]], a [[marine (ocean)|marine]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Eratoidae]], the false cowries or trivias.<ref name=\"WoRMS\">MolluscaBase (2018). Hespererato rehderi (Raines, 2002). Accessed through: World Register of Marine Species at: http://marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=567510 on 2018-07-18</ref>\n\n==Description==\n{{Expand section|date=January 2011}}\nThe shell grows to a length of 1.6&nbsp;mm\n\n==Distribution==\nThis species occurs in the Pacific Ocean off [[Easter Island]]\n\n==Notes==\n* Raines. 2002. Contribution to the knowledge of Easter Island Mollusca. Conchiglia 34 (304): 11-40\n* Raines, B.K. (2007) New molluscan records from Easter Island, with the description of a new Ethminolia. Visaya, 2(1), 70\u201388. page(s): 81\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q13227902}}\n\n[[Category:Eratoidae]]\n[[Category:Gastropods described in 2002]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of the Pacific Ocean]]\n", "name_user": "Dawnseeker2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hespererato_rehderi"}
{"title_page": "Filmfare Award for Best Actor \u2013 Telugu", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name           = Filmfare Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Telugu\n| description    = Best Performance by an Actor in a Leading Role in Telugu films\n| image          = Ram Charan at Promotion of 'Zanjeer' on Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa.jpg\n| caption        = The two time winner and the 2018 recipient: [[Ram Charan]]\n\n| presenter      = ''[[Filmfare]]''\n| country        = [[India]]\n| year           = [[N. T. Rama Rao]],<br> ''[[Badi Panthulu]]'' (1972)\n| holder         = [[Ram Charan]], <br> ''[[Rangasthalam]]'' ([[66th Filmfare Awards South|2018]])\n| website        = [http://filmfareawards.indiatimes.com/ Filmfare Awards]\n}}\nThe '''Filmfare Best Actor Award''' is given by the ''Filmfare'' magazine as part of its annual [[Filmfare Awards South]] for [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] films. The awards were extended to \"Best Actor\" in 1972.<ref name=\"tmr43\">[[#Film world|Film world]], p 43</ref> The year indicates the year of release of the film.\n\n==Superlatives==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Superlative\n! Actor\n! Record\n|-\n| Actor with most awards\n| [[Chiranjeevi]]\n| 7\n|-\n|Most nominations || [[Mahesh Babu]]||10\n|-\n| Actor with most nominations without ever winning\n| [[Prabhas]]\n| 7\n|-\n| Oldest winner\n| [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]]\n| 69\n|-\n| Youngest winner\n| [[Uday Kiran]]\n| 21\n|-\n|}\n*[[Allu Arjun]] is the only actor to win Best Actor, [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Telugu|Best Supporting Actor]] awards and [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actor \u2013 South|Critics Award for Best Actor]] and first actor to win any both of them.\n*[[Sobhan Babu]] was the most victorious actor with four wins in the 70s. In the 80's, [[Kamal Hassan]] won this award for three times. [[Chiranjeevi]] ruled the 90's with three wins and 2000's with two wins. Until now, [[Mahesh Babu]] is the most successful actor in 2010s with three wins.\n\n== Multiple Winners ==\n* '''7 Wins''' : [[Chiranjeevi]]\n* '''5 Wins''' : [[Mahesh Babu]] \n* '''4 Wins''' : [[Sobhan Babu]], [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]]\n* '''3 Wins''' : [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]], [[Kamal Haasan]], [[Krishnam Raju]], [[Allu Arjun]]\n* '''2 Wins''' : [[Dr. Rajasekhar (actor)|Rajasekhar]], [[N. T. Rama Rao Jr.]] & [[Ram Charan]]\n* '''Youngest Winner''' : [[Uday Kiran]]\n\n==Winners==\n<!-- DO NOT EITHER ADD UNSOURCED CONTENT OR CHANGE SOURCED CONTENT !-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" style=\"width:50%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#d1e4fd;\"\n! Year || Actor ||Role || Film || Ref\n|-style=\"background:#edf3fe;\"\n| [[66th Filmfare Awards South|2018]] || '''[[Ram Charan]]''' || Chittibabu || ''[[Rangasthalam]]'' || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/winners-of-the-66th-filmfare-awards-south-2019_-38163.html|title=Winners of the 66th Filmfare Awards (South) 2019|website=[[Filmfare]]|accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[65th Filmfare Awards South|2017]] || '''[[Vijay Deverakonda]]''' || Dr. Arjun Reddy Deshmukh || ''[[Arjun Reddy]]'' || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/features/winners-of-the-65th-jio-filmfare-awards-south-2018_-28887.html|title=Winners of the 65th Jio Filmfare Awards (South) 2018 - filmfare.com|website=www.filmfare.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[64th Filmfare Awards South|2016]] || '''[[Jr. NTR]]''' ||Abhiram|| ''[[Naanaku Prematho]]'' || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/winners-of-the-64th-jio-filmfare-awards-south-21594.html|title=Winners of the 64th Jio Filmfare Awards (South) - filmfare.com|website=www.filmfare.com}}</ref>\n|-style=\"background:#edf3fe;\"\n| [[63rd Filmfare Awards South|2015]] || '''[[Mahesh Babu]]''' ||Harsha Vardhan|| ''[[Srimanthudu]]'' || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/winners-of-the-63rd-britannia-filmfare-awards-south-13996.html|title=Winners of the 63rd Britannia Filmfare